	   <tr><td colspan=2>From everything I've read, these armor quests appear to be quite challenging.<br><br>Clickable Effect: shield of lava?&nbsp;&nbsp;Summon bandages?  How about Focus effect: FT, of any level.<br><br>Haven't we earned that by this level?  <br><br>Don't get me wrong, the other stats on the robe are quite nice and most magicians would benefit from wearing it.  I just wish the effects were more in line with the difficulty of obtaining the robe.<br><br>On another note; for those tank types that have commented we magicians just sit on our butts and toss in a nuke when the mood strikes us while our pets do all our dirty work:<br><br>/rant on - You clearly have no idea what it means to be a magician.  We are slaves to our mana regeneration.  Nuking too often or too early is a fast track to the top of the mob's hate list.  Doesn't that make <i>your</i> job tougher?  So yes, we don't start nuking right away.  Yes, we don't want to nuke too often.  Yes, we must spend a lot of time sitting and watching our mana bar refill oh-so-slowly, while you pull mobs non-stop.  <br><br>While I'm sitting there my pet is at your side helping pummel your opponant, or better yet, being set on those troublesome adds to keep them occupied, take the hits, and mete out damage until you have time to get to them.  Doesn't that make your job easier?  These are some things magicians contribute while we're just &quot;sitting on our butts&quot;. /rant off<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Jan 23 16:36:23 2003</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Merry meet, merry part, and merry meet again.<br><br>Yanari, Witch of Felwithe</td></tr>
